Simple Method for Transpose

Function simpleTranspose(Array sparseMatrix, Integer numElements, Integer numRows, Integer numCols)
    // Create a new array for the transposed matrix
    Array transposed[numElements] of SparseMatrixElement
    
    // Iterate through each element in the original sparse matrix
    For i from 0 to numElements - 1 do
        transposed[i].row = sparseMatrix[i].col
        transposed[i].col = sparseMatrix[i].row
        transposed[i].value = sparseMatrix[i].value
    End For
    
    Return transposed
End Function



Fast Transpose Method

Function fastTranspose(Array sparseMatrix, Integer numElements, Integer numRows, Integer numCols)
    // Create an array to count the number of elements in each column
    Array count[numCols] of Integer initialized to 0
    
    // Count the number of elements in each column
    For i from 0 to numElements - 1 do
        count[sparseMatrix[i].col] = count[sparseMatrix[i].col] + 1
    End For
    
    // Create an array to store the starting index for each column in the transposed matrix
    Array index[numCols] of Integer initialized to 0
    index[0] = 0
    
    // Calculate the starting index for each column
    For j from 1 to numCols - 1 do
        index[j] = index[j - 1] + count[j - 1]
    End For
    
    // Create a new array for the transposed matrix
    Array transposed[numElements] of SparseMatrixElement
    
    // Fill the transposed matrix using the starting indices
    For i from 0 to numElements - 1 do
        j = sparseMatrix[i].col
        transposed[index[j]].row = sparseMatrix[i].col
        transposed[index[j]].col = sparseMatrix[i].row
        transposed[index[j]].value = sparseMatrix[i].value
        index[j] = index[j] + 1
    End For
    
    Return transposed
End Function



Simple Transpose Method:
This method iterates through each element of the original sparse matrix and swaps the row and column indices to create the transposed matrix. The runtime is (O(\text{columns} \times \text{elements})) because it processes each element once.

Fast Transpose Method:
This method first counts the number of elements in each column and calculates the starting index for each column in the transposed matrix. It then fills the transposed matrix using these indices. The runtime is (O(\text{columns} + \text{elements})) because it processes the elements and columns separately.
